            <!-- Article Content -->
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 content-section">
                <p>As Kalamazoo homeowners know all too well, Michigan's diverse weather patterns can take a serious toll on residential roofs. From heavy snow in winter to intense summer storms, your roof faces constant challenges. Recognizing the early warning signs of roof damage can save you thousands in repairs and protect your home from devastating structural issues.</p><h2>1. Water Stains and Active Leaks</h2><p>If you notice brown or yellow stains on your ceiling or walls, you're likely dealing with an active roof leak. These water spots often indicate serious roofing issues that require <a href='/services/emergency-roof-services'>emergency roof services</a>. Our team frequently encounters this problem in older homes throughout <a href='/areas-we-serve/portage-'>Portage</a> and <a href='/areas-we-serve/richland-'>Richland</a>.</p><h2>2. Missing or Damaged Shingles</h2><p>After severe weather events, inspect your roof for:</p><ul><li>Curling or buckling shingles</li><li>Bare spots where granules are missing</li><li>Completely missing shingles</li><li>Cracked or broken shingles</li></ul><p>These issues require immediate <a href='/services/roof-repair'>roof repair</a> to prevent water infiltration.</p><h2>3. Sagging Roof Deck</h2><p>A sagging roofline is never normal and often indicates structural problems. If you notice any dips or waves in your roof's surface, schedule an immediate <a href='/services/roof-inspection'>roof inspection</a>. This issue is particularly common in older homes throughout <a href='/areas-we-serve/texas-charter-township-'>Texas Charter Township</a>.</p><h2>4. Daylight Through Roof Boards</h2><p>Check your attic during daylight hours. If you can see sunlight peeking through the roof boards, you have serious gaps that need addressing. This problem often leads to the issues discussed in our guide about <a href='/blog/the-hidden-dangers-of-ignoring-minor-roof-leaks'>The Hidden Dangers of Ignoring Minor Roof Leaks</a>.</p><h2>5. Excessive Granules in Gutters</h2><p>While some granule loss is normal, especially with new shingles, large amounts in your gutters indicate advanced wear. This often means your roof is nearing the end of its lifespan and may need <a href='/services/roof-installation'>roof installation</a> services.</p><h3>Why Immediate Action is Critical</h3><p>Delaying roof repairs in Kalamazoo's climate can lead to:</p><ul><li>Structural damage</li><li>Mold growth</li><li>Higher energy bills</li><li>Decreased property value</li></ul><p>Learn more about weather impacts in our article on <a href='/blog/how-seasonal-weather-affects-the-lifespan-of-your-roof'>How Seasonal Weather Affects the Lifespan of Your Roof</a>.</p><h3>Don't Wait Until It's Too Late</h3><p>If you notice any of these warning signs, don't delay. Contact Kalamazoo Roofing Contractors at (555) 666-7777 for a comprehensive roof inspection. Our experienced team serves the entire Kalamazoo area, including <a href='/areas-we-serve/oshtemo-charter-township-'>Oshtemo Charter Township</a> and surrounding communities.</p><p>Schedule your inspection today and protect your home from costly damage. Remember, early intervention can save thousands in repairs and extend your roof's lifespan significantly.</p>
